OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Much of the UK is experiencing a       
OL,6, heatwave, with temperatures expected to
OL,7, rise even further to hit up to 42C     
OL,8, (107.6F).                              
OL,10,FPeople have been advised to avoid      
OL,11,Fnon-essential travel and many have been
OL,12,Fworking from home. Some schools have   
OL,13,Fclosed early, or chosen not to open at 
OL,14,Fall, while the extreme heat is putting 
OL,15,Fpressure on the health service.        
OL,17,FBut countries where temperatures are   
OL,18,Fusually higher have adapted their      
OL,19,Finfrastructure and lifestyle to cope   
OL,20,Fwith the heat. Our correspondents      
OL,21,Fexplain how.                           
